These Boots  
  
  *figured out a song, not even vaguely goth, but a great deal of fun to play.*  
  *;-) use if you want.*  
  *these boots are made for walkin'-nancy sinatra*  
  *this is really simply, all chords can be played as power chords for*  
  *simplicity's sake and cus it sounds just fine that way :-)*  
  *for the slide bit, just start at the bottem and work up, you should finish on a*  
  *intro/main part: ***D***, a slide to ***C*** for embellishment ala the slide in the verse*  
  *parts for gimme shelter.*  
  *riff 2: ***A*** & ***G***  
  *chorus: ***G*** & ***E***  
  *repeats 3 times :-)*<!--n:These Boots:s:18798:e:878-->
